				h2 My frst marathon experience.

			article
				p Exactly one year ago, when we had just moved to Paris, the marathon passed our appartment in Rue Saint Antoine. Seeing all these people pass me by impressed me so much that I decided I had to conquer the marathon myself.
				
				figure
					img(src='http://ourparisadventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/marathon.jpg', alt="2014. The Paris marathon in Rue Saint Antoine.")
					figcaption 2014. The Paris marathon in Rue Saint Antoine.

				p I gave myself five months to prepare. After running on and off for a couple of years it was time to get serious. As I work for #[a(href='http://akqa.com/work') AKQA] I naturally chose to train with the nike+ app and all the related products.
				p Nike's marathon training program was brutal. Even at the rookie level it made me run 5 times a week from the get-go. Both my endurance and cardio vascular strength were shit after living the good life in Paris for a year. Luckily the distances were short for the first couple of weeks.

